{"key":"processedPost-13497159","value":{"id":13497159,"first":13496266,"last":13497202,"when":1290010788,"utime":"11/17/10 06:19 PM","content":"After mixing the water and vermiculite, there should&nbsp; be <i>zero water</i> in the bottom of the bowl before adding the rice flour.&nbsp; If there is, colonization will be very slow and this in turn opens the door for contaminants.&nbsp; Wet substrates colonize slow if at all, while substrates on the dry side colonize very fast.&nbsp; You're going to dunk before first flush to add the water for fruiting, so there's no need to get it too wet before inoculation.<br /><br />All of this is covered in detail for visual learners in the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek video</a>.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pf tek. Should verm absorb all water from recipe?"}}